{{Youmay|the [[Ore/Legends|ore]] in the [[Star Wars Legends|''Star Wars'' Legends]] continuity|the [[canon]] individual [[Ba'kif]] or the real-world voice actor [[Kiff VandenHeuvel]]|linebreak=1}}
{{Quote|Barrister Snoil. You are aware of the case of Gadon Three?''"<br />"''Yes. But there are at least four cases that might have some application here. Please be more specific.''"<br />"''A matter of breakaway Kif miners.''"<br />"''Ah, yes. Approximately fifty standard years ago, the miners began selling high-energy ores on the open market. Some of these ores found their way to a colony allied with enemies of the Gadon regime. The Gadons came to the Republic for a ruling, and it was adjudged that the intent of the original sale had been above reproach. Therefore the final disposition of the ores was not the responsibility of the miners.|[[G'Mai Duris]] and [[Doolb Snoil]]|<ref name="Cestus">''[[The Cestus Deception]]''</ref>}}
'''Kif''' was a high-energy [[Ore/Legends|ore]] [[Mining/Legends|mined]] at [[Gadon 3]].<ref name="CSWE">{{CSWECite|I|306|Gadon 3}}</ref>

{{Substance-stub}}

==Behind the scenes==
The name of kif was introduced via a mention of "Kif miners" in [[Steven Barnes]]' [[2004]] novel ''[[The Cestus Deception]]'' of the [[Clone Wars multimedia project]].<ref name="Cestus" /> [[2008]]'s ''[[The Complete Star Wars Encyclopedia]]'' subsequently introduced the name's decapitalized form, "kif," and confirmed that it was in fact the name of<ref name="CSWE" /> the type of ore that the novel had associated with the miners.<ref name="Cestus" />

